<subSubSection id="C36CF3DEFFA7DC17FF4FFDA4FEED4717" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC9A055FFA7DC17FF4FFDA4FEED4717" blockId="9.[151,1437,474,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">
Distribution. 
<collectingCountry id="F361E0C5FFA7DC17FEF6FDA4FECF463F" box="[302,373,547,573]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">China</collectingCountry>
. Record of this species from 
<collectingCountry id="F361E0C5FFA7DC17FD1BFDA4FC92463F" box="[707,808,547,573]" name="Romania" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">Romania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7DDA4FFA7DC17FCE0FDA4FB91463F" author="Obraztsov, N. S." box="[824,1067,546,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref7618" refString="Obraztsov, N. S. (1964) Die Gattungen der Palaearktischen Tortricidae. II. Die Unterfamilie Olethreutinae. 5 Teil. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 107 (1), 1 - 48 (131 - 178), taf. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1964">Obraztsov 1964: 151</bibRefCitation>
; Razowski 1996: 146, 1999: 44, 2003: 61) is based on incorrect interpretation of 
<typeStatus id="54CD1EF7FFA7DC17FD3EFDC0FCAC4663" box="[742,790,583,609]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76DBD6FFA7DC17FC40FDC0FB9D4663" authorityName="Caradja" authorityYear="1928" box="[920,1063,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Semasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tscheliana">
<emphasis id="B9027C47FFA7DC17FC40FDC0FB9D4663" box="[920,1063,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">S. tscheliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species was described from single male collected in “Mountains west of Beijing” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7DDA4FFA7DC17FCE1FDECFBAB4687" author="Caradja, A." box="[825,1041,619,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" pagination="361 - 428" refId="ref6424" refString="Caradja, A. (1928) Die Kleinfalter der Stotzner'schen Ausbeute, nebst Zutraege aus meiner Sammlung [Zweite biogeographische Skizze: &quot; Zentralasien &quot;]. Analele Academiei Romane. Memoriile Secțiunii Stiințifice, Seria III, Tomul IV, 361 - 428." type="journal article" year="1928">Caradja 1928: 361</bibRefCitation>
, 388, 392), but not from 
<collectingCountry id="F361E0C5FFA7DC17FAEFFDECFA264687" box="[1335,1436,619,645]" name="Romania" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">Romania</collectingCountry>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7DDA4FFA7DC17FEEAFD08FE4A46AB" author="Lepiforum" box="[306,496,655,681]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" refId="ref7453" refString="Lepiforum (2022) Genus Thiodia Hubner [1825]. Available from: http // www. lepiforum. de (accessed 9 February 2022)" type="book" year="2022">Lepiforum 2022</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7DDA4FFA7DC17FDDCFD08FD5046AB" author="Caradja, A." box="[516,746,655,681]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" pagination="361 - 428" refId="ref6424" refString="Caradja, A. (1928) Die Kleinfalter der Stotzner'schen Ausbeute, nebst Zutraege aus meiner Sammlung [Zweite biogeographische Skizze: &quot; Zentralasien &quot;]. Analele Academiei Romane. Memoriile Secțiunii Stiințifice, Seria III, Tomul IV, 361 - 428." type="journal article" year="1928">Caradja (1928: 392)</bibRefCitation>
indicated affinity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76DBD6FFA7DC17FC05FD08FBD446AB" authorityName="Caradja" authorityYear="1928" box="[989,1134,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Semasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tscheliana">
<emphasis id="B9027C47FFA7DC17FC05FD08FBD446AB" box="[989,1134,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">S. tscheliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C76DBD6FFA7DC17FB4EFD08FA8746AB" authorityName="Kennel" authorityYear="1908" box="[1174,1341,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Thiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatoliana">
<emphasis id="B9027C47FFA7DC17FB4EFD08FA8746AB" box="[1174,1341,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">Th. anatoliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B9027C47FFA7DC17FAA0FD08FE8446CF" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">
<taxonomicName id="4C76DBD6FFA7DC17FAA0FD08FE8046CF" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Grapholitha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="placidana">Th. placidana</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7DDA4FFA7DC17FE91FD34FDEB46CF" author="Obraztsov, N. S." box="[329,593,690,717]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref7618" refString="Obraztsov, N. S. (1964) Die Gattungen der Palaearktischen Tortricidae. II. Die Unterfamilie Olethreutinae. 5 Teil. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 107 (1), 1 - 48 (131 - 178), taf. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1964">Obraztsov (1964: 151)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="4C76DBD6FFA7DC17FD3AFD34FCCC46CF" authorityName="Caradja" authorityYear="1928" box="[738,886,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Semasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tscheliana">
<emphasis id="B9027C47FFA7DC17FD3AFD34FCCC46CF" box="[738,886,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">S. tscheliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in “species incertae sedis” within 
<taxonomicName id="4C76DBD6FFA7DC17FACDFD34FAD646CF" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[1301,1388,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Thiodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9027C47FFA7DC17FACDFD34FAD646CF" box="[1301,1388,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">Thiodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but gave no details supporting this decision. The systematic position of the species is uncertain until 
<typeStatus id="54CD1EF7FFA7DC17FAD4FD50FA8646F3" box="[1292,1340,727,753]" pageId="9" pageNumber="467">type</typeStatus>
remains unexamined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
